pathetao_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
pathetao_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.comment: The quantity with standard name sea_water_added_potential_temperature is a passive tracer in an ocean model whose surface flux does not come from the atmosphere but is imposed externally upon the simulated climate system. The surface flux is expressed as a heat flux and converted to a passive tracer increment as if it were a heat flux being added to potential temperature. The passive tracer is transported within the ocean as if it were potential temperature. The passive tracer is zero in the control climate of the model. The passive tracer records added heat, as described for the CMIP6 FAFMIP experiment (doi:10.5194/gmd-9-3993-2016), following earlier ideas. Potential temperature is the temperature a parcel of air or sea water would have if moved adiabatically to sea level pressure.

pbfe_yr-oc-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
pbfe_yr-oc-tav-l-hxy.comment: 'Mole concentration' means number of moles per unit volume, also called 'molarity', and is used in the construction mole_concentration_of_X_in_Y, where X is a material constituent of Y.  A chemical or biological species denoted by X may be described by a single term such as 'nitrogen' or a phrase such as 'nox_expressed_as_nitrogen'. The specification of a physical process by the phrase due_to_process means that the quantity named is a  single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity  named by omitting the phrase.  'tendency_of_X' means derivative of X with respect to time.

prbigthetao_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
prbigthetao_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.comment: A passive tracer in an ocean model which is subject to an externally imposed perturbative surface heat flux. The passive tracer is initialised to the conservative temperature in the control climate before the perturbation is imposed. Its surface flux is the heat flux from the atmosphere, not including the imposed perturbation, and is converted to a passive tracer increment as if it were being added to conservative temperature. prthetao_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
prthetao_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.comment: A passive tracer in an ocean model which is subject to an externally imposed perturbative surface heat flux. The passive tracer is initialised to the potential temperature in the control climate before the perturbation is imposed. Its surface flux is the heat flux from the atmosphere, not including the imposed perturbation, and is converted to a passive tracer increment as if it were being added to potential temperature. The passive tracer is transported within the ocean as if it were potential temperature.

rhc13_mon-ld-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where land time: mean
rhc13_mon-ld-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Heterotrophic respiration is respiration by heterotrophs ('consumers'), which are organisms (including animals and decomposers) that consume other organisms or dead organic material, rather than synthesising organic material from inorganic precursors using energy from the environment (especially sunlight) as autotrophs ('producers') do. Heterotrophic respiration goes on within both the soil and litter pools.

rlds_3hr-ap-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The surface called 'surface' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere. 'longwave' means longwave radiation. Downwelling radiation is radiation from above. It does not mean 'net downward'. When thought of as being incident on a surface, a radiative flux is sometimes called 'irradiance'. In addition, it is identical with the quantity measured by a cosine-collector light-meter and sometimes called 'vector irradiance'. In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, 'flux' implies per unit area, called 'flux density' in physics.

When thought of as being incident on a surface, a radiative flux is sometimes called 'irradiance'.  In addition, it is identical with the quantity measured by a cosine-collector light-meter and sometimes called 'vector irradiance'.  In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, 'flux' implies per unit area, called 'flux density' in physics.  'shortwave' means shortwave radiation.
rsdo_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Downwelling Shortwave Radiation in Sea Water

rsdoabsorb_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
rsdoabsorb_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.comment: 'shortwave' means shortwave radiation. 'Layer' means any layer with upper and lower boundaries that have constant values in some vertical coordinate. There must be a vertical coordinate variable indicating the extent of the layer(s). If the layers are model layers, the vertical coordinate can be model_level_number, but it is recommended to specify a physical coordinate (in a scalar or auxiliary coordinate variable) as well. Net absorbed radiation is the difference between absorbed and emitted radiation.
rsdoabsorb_mon-op-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Net Rate of Absorption of Shortwave Energy in Ocean Layer

rsus_3hr-ap-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The surface called 'surface' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere. 'shortwave' means shortwave radiation. Upwelling radiation is radiation from below. It does not mean 'net upward'. When thought of as being incident on a surface, a radiative flux is sometimes called 'irradiance'. In addition, it is identical with the quantity measured by a cosine-collector light-meter and sometimes called 'vector irradiance'. In accordance with common usage in geophysical disciplines, 'flux' implies per unit area, called 'flux density' in physics.

rzwc_day-ld-tav-z0-hxy.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area. The content of a soil layer is the vertical integral of the specified quantity within the layer. The quantity with standard name mass_content_of_water_in_soil_layer_defined_by_root_depth is the vertical integral between the surface and the depth to which plant roots penetrate. A coordinate variable or scalar coordinate variable with standard name root_depth can be used to specify the extent of the layer. 'Water' means water in all phases.

sicompstren_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Computed strength of the ice pack, defined as the energy (J m-2) dissipated per unit area removed from the ice pack under compression, and assumed proportional to the change in potential energy caused by ridging. For Hibler-type models, this is P (= P*h exp(-C(1-A)) where P* is compressive strength, h ice thickness, A compactness and C strength reduction constant).

sidmassdyn_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Total change in sea-ice mass through dynamics-related processes (advection,...) divided by grid-cell area

sidmassevapsubl_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sidmassevapsubl_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The rate of change of sea-ice mass change through evaporation and sublimation divided by grid-cell area
sidmassevapsubl_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Ice Mass Change Through Evaporation and Sublimation

sidmassgrowthbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sidmassgrowthbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The rate of change of sea ice mass due to vertical growth of existing sea ice at its base divided by grid-cell area.
sidmassgrowthbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Ice Mass Change Through Basal Growth

sidmassgrowthwat_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sidmassgrowthwat_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The rate of change of sea ice mass due to sea ice formation in supercooled water (often through frazil formation) divided by grid-cell area. Together, sidmassgrowthwat and sidmassgrowthbot should give total ice growth
sidmassgrowthwat_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Ice Mass Change Through Growth in Supercooled Open Water (Frazil)

sidmasslat_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sidmasslat_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The rate of change of sea ice mass through lateral melting divided by grid-cell area (report 0 if not explicitly calculated thermodynamically)

sidmassmeltbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sidmassmeltbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The rate of change of sea ice mass through melting at the ice bottom divided by grid-cell area
sidmassmeltbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Ice Mass Change Through Bottom Melting

sidmassmelttop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sidmassmelttop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The rate of change of sea ice mass through melting at the ice surface divided by grid-cell area
sidmassmelttop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Ice Mass Change Through Surface Melting

sidmasssi_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sidmasssi_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The rate of change of sea ice mass due to transformation of snow to sea ice divided by grid-cell area
sidmasssi_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Ice Mass Change Through Snow-to-Ice Conversion

sidmassth_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sidmassth_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Total change in sea-ice mass from thermodynamic processes divided by grid-cell area

sidmasstranx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Includes transport of both sea ice and snow by advection

sidmasstrany_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Includes transport of both sea ice and snow by advection

sidragbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sidragbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Oceanic drag coefficient that is used to calculate the oceanic momentum drag on sea ice

sidragtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sidragtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Atmospheric drag coefficient that is used to calculate the atmospheric momentum drag on sea ice

siextentn_mon-si-tav-z0-hm.comment: Total area of all Northern-Hemisphere grid cells that are covered by at least 15 % areal fraction of sea ice

siextents_mon-si-tav-z0-hm.comment: Total area of all Southern-Hemisphere grid cells that are covered by at least 15 % areal fraction of sea ice

sifb_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sifb_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Mean height of sea-ice surface (=snow-ice interface when snow covered) above sea level

siflcondbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siflcondbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: the net heat conduction flux at the ice base
siflcondbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Net Conductive Heat Fluxes in Ice at the Bottom

siflcondtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siflcondtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: the net heat conduction flux at the ice surface
siflcondtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Net Conductive Heat Flux in Ice at the Surface

siflfwbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siflfwbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Total flux of fresh water from water into sea ice divided by grid-cell area; This flux is negative during ice growth (liquid water mass decreases, hence upward flux of freshwater), positive during ice melt (liquid water mass increases, hence downward flux of freshwater)

siflfwdrain_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siflfwdrain_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Total flux of fresh water from sea-ice surface into underlying ocean. This combines both surface melt water that drains directly into the ocean and the drainage of surface melt pond. By definition, this flux is always positive.

sifllatstop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconca)
sifllatstop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: the net latent heat flux over sea ice
sifllatstop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Net Latent Heat Flux over Sea Ice

sifllwdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconca)
sifllwdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: the downwelling longwave flux over sea ice (always positive)
sifllwdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Downwelling Longwave Flux over Sea Ice

sifllwutop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconca)
sifllwutop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: the upwelling longwave flux over sea ice (always negative)
sifllwutop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Upwelling Longwave Flux over Sea Ice

siflsenstop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconca)
siflsenstop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: the net sensible heat flux over sea ice
siflsenstop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Net Upward Sensible Heat Flux over Sea Ice

siflsensupbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siflsensupbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: the net sensible heat flux under sea ice from the ocean
siflsensupbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Net Upward Sensible Heat Flux Under Sea Ice

siflswdbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siflswdbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The downwelling shortwave flux underneath sea ice (always positive)
siflswdbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Downwelling Shortwave Flux Under Sea Ice

siflswdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconca)
siflswdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The downwelling shortwave flux over sea ice (always positive by sign convention)
siflswdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Downwelling Shortwave Flux over Sea Ice

siflswutop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconca)
siflswutop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The upwelling shortwave flux over sea ice (always negative)
siflswutop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Upwelling Shortwave Flux over Sea Ice

siforcecoriolx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siforcecoriolx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: X-component of force on sea ice caused by coriolis force
siforcecoriolx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Coriolis Force Term in Force Balance (X-Component)

siforcecorioly_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siforcecorioly_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Y-component of force on sea ice caused by coriolis force
siforcecorioly_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Coriolis Force Term in Force Balance (Y-Component)

siforceintstrx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siforceintstrx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: X-component of force on sea ice caused by internal stress (divergence of sigma)
siforceintstrx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Internal Stress Term in Force Balance (X-Component)

siforceintstry_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siforceintstry_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Y-component of force on sea ice caused by internal stress (divergence of sigma)
siforceintstry_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Internal Stress Term in Force Balance (Y-Component)

siforcetiltx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siforcetiltx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: X-component of force on sea ice caused by sea-surface tilt
siforcetiltx_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Surface Tilt Term in Force Balance (X-Component)

siforcetilty_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siforcetilty_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Y-component of force on sea ice caused by sea-surface tilt
siforcetilty_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Surface Tilt Term in Force Balance (Y-Component)

sihc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sihc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Heat content of all ice in grid cell divided by total grid-cell area. Water at 0 Celsius is assumed to have a heat content of 0 J.  Does not include heat content of snow, but does include heat content of brine. Heat content is always negative, since both the sensible and the latent heat content of ice are less than that of water
sihc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Ice Heat Content per Unit Area

siitdconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siitdconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Percentage of grid cell covered by each ice-thickness category (vector with one entry for each thickness category starting from the thinnest category, netcdf file should use thickness bounds of the categories as third coordinate axis)
siitdconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Sea-Ice Area Percentages in Thickness Categories

siitdsnconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siitdconc)
siitdsnconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Percentage of grid cell covered by snow in each ice-thickness category (vector with one entry for each thickness category starting from the thinnest category, netcdf file should use thickness bounds of the categories as third coordinate axis)
siitdsnconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Snow Area Percentages in Ice Thickness Categories

siitdsnthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siitdconc)
siitdsnthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Actual thickness of snow in each  category (NOT volume divided by grid area),  (vector with one entry for each thickness category starting from the thinnest category, netcdf file should use thickness bounds of categories as third coordinate axis)
siitdsnthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Snow Thickness in Ice Thickness Categories

siitdthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siitdconc)
siitdthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Actual (floe) thickness of sea ice in each  category (NOT volume divided by grid area),  (vector with one entry for each thickness category starting from the thinnest category, netcdf file should use thickness bounds of categories as third coordinate axis)

siltfrac_fx-ap-none-l-hxy.comment: Volume fraction of silt in soil

simass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
simass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Total mass of sea ice divided by grid-cell area

simassacrossline_mon-si-tav-z0-hm.comment: net (sum of transport in all directions) sea ice area transport through the following four passages, positive into the Arctic Ocean 1. Fram Strait = (11.5W,81.3N to (10.5E,79.6N) 2. Canadian Archipelago = (128.2W,70.6N) to (59.3W,82.1N) 3. Barents opening = (16.8E,76.5N) to (19.2E,70.2N) 4. Bering Strait = (171W,66.2N) to (166W,65N)
simassacrossline_mon-si-tav-z0-hm.long_name: Sea Mass Area Flux Through Straits

simpconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
simpconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Percentage of sea ice, by area, which is covered by melt ponds, giving equal weight to every square metre of sea ice .
simpconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Percentage Cover of Sea Ice by Meltpond

simpmass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice_melt_pond (comment: mask=simpconc)
simpmass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Meltpond Mass per Unit Area (as Depth)

simprefrozen_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice_melt_pond (comment: mask=simpconc)
simprefrozen_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Volume of refrozen ice on melt ponds divided by meltpond covered area
simprefrozen_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Thickness of Refrozen Ice on Melt Pond

sios_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sios_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Mole concentration means number of moles per unit volume, also called 'molarity', and is used in the construction 'mole_concentration_of_X_in_Y', where X is a material constituent of Y. A chemical or biological species denoted by X may be described by a single term such as 'nitrogen' or a phrase such as 'nox_expressed_as_nitrogen'. 'Dissolved inorganic silicon' means the sum of all inorganic silicon in solution (including silicic acid and its first dissociated anion SiO(OH)3-).
sios_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Surface Total Dissolved Inorganic Silicon Concentration

sipr_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sipr_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: mass of liquid precipitation falling onto sea ice divided by grid-cell area

sirdgconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sirdgconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Fraction of sea ice, by area, which is covered by sea ice ridges, giving equal weight to every square metre of sea ice .
sirdgconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Percentage Cover of Sea Ice by Ridging

sirdgthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice_ridges (comment: mask=sirdgconc)
sirdgthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Sea Ice Ridge Height (representing mean height over the ridged area)

sisali_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sisali_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Mean sea-ice salinity of all sea ice in grid cell

sisaltmass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sisaltmass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Total mass of all salt in sea ice divided by grid-cell area
sisaltmass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Mass of Salt in Sea Ice per Area

sishevel_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc) time: point
sishevel_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.comment: Maximum shear of sea-ice velocity field (second shear strain invariant)
sishevel_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.long_name: Maximum Shear of Sea-Ice Velocity Field

sisnconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sisnconc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Percentage of sea ice, by area, which is covered by snow, giving equal weight to every square metre of sea ice . Exclude snow that lies on land or land ice.

sisnhc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sisnhc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Heat-content of all snow in grid cell divided by total grid-cell area. Snow-water equivalent at 0 Celsius is assumed to have a heat content of 0 J.  Does not include heat content of sea ice.
sisnhc_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Snow Heat Content per Unit Area

sisnmass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sisnmass_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Total mass of snow on sea ice divided by sea-ice area.

sisnthick_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where snow over sea_ice area: time: mean where sea_ice
sisnthick_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Actual thickness of snow (snow volume divided by snow-covered area)

sisnthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where snow over sea_ice area: time: mean where sea_ice
sisnthick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Actual thickness of snow (snow volume divided by snow-covered area)

sispeed_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sispeed_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Speed of ice (i.e. mean absolute velocity) to account for back-and-forth movement of the ice

sispeed_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sispeed_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Speed of ice (i.e. mean absolute velocity) to account for back-and-forth movement of the ice

sistremax_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc) time: point
sistremax_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.comment: Maximum shear stress in sea ice (second stress invariant)
sistremax_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.long_name: Maximum Shear Stress in Sea Ice

sistresave_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc) time: point
sistresave_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.comment: Average normal stress in sea ice (first stress invariant)
sistresave_mon-si-tpt-z0-hxy.long_name: Average Normal Stress in Sea Ice

sistrxdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sistrxdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: X-component of atmospheric stress on sea ice
sistrxdtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: X-Component of Atmospheric Stress on Sea Ice

sistrxubot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sistrxubot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: X-component of ocean stress on sea ice
sistrxubot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: X-Component of Ocean Stress on Sea Ice

sistrydtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sistrydtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Y-component of atmospheric stress on sea ice
sistrydtop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Y-Component of Atmospheric Stress on Sea Ice

sistryubot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sistryubot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Y-component of ocean stress on sea ice
sistryubot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Y-Component of Ocean Stress on Sea Ice

sitempbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sitempbot_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Report temperature at interface, NOT temperature within lowermost model layer

sitempsnic_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sitempsnic_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Report surface temperature of ice where snow thickness is zero

sitemptop_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sitemptop_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Report surface temperature of snow where snow covers the sea ice.

sitemptop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sitemptop_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Report surface temperature of snow where snow covers the sea ice.

sithick_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sithick_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Actual (floe) thickness of sea ice (NOT volume divided by grid area as was done in CMIP5)

sithick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
sithick_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Actual (floe) thickness of sea ice (NOT volume divided by grid area as was done in CMIP5)

sitimefrac_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sitimefrac_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Fraction of time steps of the averaging period during which sea ice is present (siconc >0 ) in a grid cell
sitimefrac_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Fraction of Time Steps with Sea Ice

sitimefrac_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sitimefrac_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Fraction of time steps of the averaging period during which sea ice is present (siconc >0 ) in a grid cell
sitimefrac_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Fraction of Time Steps with Sea Ice

siu_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siu_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The x-velocity of ice on native model grid

siu_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siu_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The x-velocity of ice on native model grid

siv_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siv_day-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The y-velocity of ice on native model grid

siv_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: time: mean where sea_ice (comment: mask=siconc)
siv_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The y-velocity of ice on native model grid

sivol_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
sivol_mon-si-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Total volume of sea ice divided by grid-cell area (this used to be called ice thickness in CMIP5)

sivoln_mon-si-tav-z0-hm.comment: total volume of sea ice in the Northern hemisphere

sivols_mon-si-tav-z0-hm.comment: total volume of sea ice in the Southern hemisphere

sltbasin_mon-op-tav-z0-hys.cell_methods: longitude: sum (comment: basin sum [along zig-zag grid path]) depth: sum time: mean

slthick_fx-ld-none-l-hxy.comment: 'Thickness' means the vertical extent of a layer. 'Cell' refers to a model grid cell.

sltovgyre_mon-op-tav-z0-hys.cell_methods: longitude: sum (comment: basin sum [along zig-zag grid path]) depth: sum time: mean
sltovgyre_mon-op-tav-z0-hys.comment: From all advective mass transport processes, resolved and parameterized.
sltovgyre_mon-op-tav-z0-hys.long_name: Northward Ocean Salt Transport Due to Gyre

sltovovrt_mon-op-tav-z0-hys.cell_methods: longitude: sum (comment: basin sum [along zig-zag grid path]) depth: sum time: mean
sltovovrt_mon-op-tav-z0-hys.comment: From all advective mass transport processes, resolved and parameterized.

spco2_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
spco2_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.comment: The surface called 'surface' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere. The partial pressure of a dissolved gas in sea water is the partial pressure in air with which it would be in equilibrium. The partial pressure of a gaseous constituent of air is the pressure which it alone would exert with unchanged temperature and number of moles per unit volume. The chemical formula for carbon dioxide is CO2.
spco2_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.long_name: Surface Aqueous Partial Pressure of CO2

spco2abio_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
spco2abio_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.comment: The surface called 'surface' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere. The chemical formula for carbon dioxide is CO2. In ocean biogeochemistry models, an 'abiotic analogue' is used to simulate the effect on a modelled variable when biological effects on ocean carbon concentration and alkalinity are ignored. The partial pressure of a gaseous constituent of air is the pressure which it alone would exert with unchanged temperature and number of moles per unit volume. The partial pressure of a dissolved gas in sea water is the partial pressure in air with which it would be in equilibrium. The partial pressure difference between sea water and air is positive when the partial pressure of the dissolved gas in sea water is greater than the partial pressure in air.
spco2abio_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.long_name: Abiotic Surface Aqueous Partial Pressure of CO2

spco2nat_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
spco2nat_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.comment: The surface called 'surface' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere. The chemical formula for carbon dioxide is CO2. In ocean biogeochemistry models, a 'natural analogue' is used to simulate the effect on a modelled variable of imposing preindustrial atmospheric carbon dioxide concentrations, even when the model as a whole may be subjected to varying forcings. The partial pressure of a gaseous constituent of air is the pressure which it alone would exert with unchanged temperature and number of moles per unit volume. The partial pressure of a dissolved gas in sea water is the partial pressure in air with which it would be in equilibrium. The partial pressure difference between sea water and air is positive when the partial pressure of the dissolved gas in sea water is greater than the partial pressure in air.
spco2nat_mon-oc-tav-z00-hxy.long_name: Natural Surface Aqueous Partial Pressure of CO2

tnhusd_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.comment: Tendency of specific humidity due to numerical diffusion.This includes any horizontal or vertical numerical moisture diffusion not associated with the parametrized moist physics or the resolved dynamics.  For example, any vertical diffusion which is part of the boundary layer mixing scheme should be excluded, as should any diffusion which is included in the terms from the resolved dynamics.   This term is required to check the closure of the moisture budget.
tnhusd_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Tendency of Specific Humidity Due to Numerical Diffusion

tnhusd_subhr-ap-tpt-l-hxys.comment: Tendency of specific humidity due to numerical diffusion.This includes any horizontal or vertical numerical moisture diffusion not associated with the parametrized moist physics or the resolved dynamics. This term is required to check the closure of the moisture budget.

tnhusmp_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.comment: Tendency of specific humidity due to model physics. This includes sources and sinks from parametrized moist physics (e.g. convection, boundary layer, stratiform condensation/evaporation, etc.) and excludes sources and sinks from resolved dynamics or from horizontal or vertical numerical diffusion not associated with model physics.  For example any diffusive mixing by the boundary layer scheme would be included.
tnhusmp_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Tendency of Specific Humidity Due to Model Physics

tnhusmp_subhr-ap-tpt-l-hxys.comment: Tendency of specific humidity due to model physics. This includes sources and sinks from parametrized moist physics (e.g. convection, boundary layer, stratiform condensation/evaporation, etc.) and excludes sources and sinks from resolved dynamics or from horizontal or vertical numerical diffusion not associated with model physics. tnhusscp_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.comment: The phrase 'tendency_of_X' means derivative of X with respect to time. 'Specific' means per unit mass. Specific humidity is the mass fraction of water vapor in (moist) air. The specification of a physical process by the phrase 'due_to_' process means that the quantity named is a single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity named by omitting the phrase. A variable with the standard name of tendency_of_specific_humidity_due_to_stratiform_cloud_and_precipitation should contain the effects of all processes which convert stratiform clouds and precipitation to or from water vapor. In an atmosphere model, stratiform cloud is that produced by large-scale convergence (not the convection schemes).
tnhusscp_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Tendency of Specific Humidity Due to Stratiform Clouds and Precipitation

tnhusscp_subhr-ap-tpt-l-hxys.comment: The phrase 'tendency_of_X' means derivative of X with respect to time. 'Specific' means per unit mass. Specific humidity is the mass fraction of water vapor in (moist) air. The specification of a physical process by the phrase 'due_to_' process means that the quantity named is a single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity named by omitting the phrase. A variable with the standard name of tendency_of_specific_humidity_due_to_stratiform_cloud_and_precipitation should contain the effects of all processes which convert stratiform clouds and precipitation to or from water vapor. In an atmosphere model, stratiform cloud is that produced by large-scale convergence (not the convection schemes).
tnhusscp_subhr-ap-tpt-l-hxys.long_name: Tendency of Specific Humidity Due to Stratiform Clouds and Precipitation

tnhusscpbl_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.comment: Tendency of Specific Humidity Due to Stratiform Cloud and Precipitation and Boundary Layer Mixing  (to be specified only in  models which do not separate budget terms for stratiform cloud, precipitation and boundary layer schemes.  Includes all boundary layer terms including and diffusive terms.)
tnhusscpbl_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Tendency of Specific Humidity Due to Stratiform Cloud and Precipitation and Boundary Layer Mixing

tnhusscpbl_subhr-ap-tpt-l-hxys.comment: Tendency of Specific Humidity Due to Stratiform Cloud and Precipitation and Boundary Layer Mixing  (to be specified only in  models which do not separate budget terms for stratiform cloud, precipitation and boundary layer schemes. tnpeot_mon-op-tcla-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean time: mean within years time: mean over years
tnpeot_mon-op-tcla-l-hxy.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area.  Potential energy is the sum of the gravitational potential energy relative to the geoid and the centripetal potential energy. (The geopotential is the specific potential energy.)  'Due to tides' means due to all astronomical gravity changes which manifest as tides.  No distinction is made between different tidal components. The specification of a physical process by the phrase due_to_process means that the quantity named is a  single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity  named by omitting the phrase.  'tendency_of_X' means derivative of X with respect to time.
tnpeot_mon-op-tcla-l-hxy.long_name: Tendency of Ocean Potential Energy Content Due to Tides

tnpeotb_mon-op-tcla-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean time: mean within years time: mean over years
tnpeotb_mon-op-tcla-l-hxy.comment: 'Content' indicates a quantity per unit area.  Potential energy is the sum of the gravitational potential energy relative to the geoid and the centripetal potential energy. (The geopotential is the specific potential energy.)  'Due to background' means caused by a time invariant imposed field which may be either constant over the globe or spatially varying, depending on the ocean model used. The specification of a physical process by the phrase due_to_process means that the quantity named is a  single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity  named by omitting the phrase.  'tendency_of_X' means derivative of X with respect to time.
tnpeotb_mon-op-tcla-l-hxy.long_name: Tendency of Ocean Potential Energy Content Due to Background

tntscp_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.comment: The phrase 'tendency_of_X' means derivative of X with respect to time. Air temperature is the bulk temperature of the air, not the surface (skin) temperature. The specification of a physical process by the phrase 'due_to_' process means that the quantity named is a single term in a sum of terms which together compose the general quantity named by omitting the phrase. A variable with the standard name tendency_of_air_temperature_due_to_stratiform_cloud_and_precipitation should contain net latent heating effects of all processes which convert stratiform clouds and precipitation between water vapour, liquid or ice phases. In an atmosphere model, stratiform cloud is that produced by large-scale convergence (not the convection schemes).
tntscp_mon-ap-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Tendency of Air Temperature Due to Stratiform Clouds and Precipitation

zfull_3hr-ap-tpt-l-hxy.comment: Height of full model levels above a reference ellipsoid. A reference ellipsoid is a mathematical figure that approximates the geoid. The geoid is a surface of constant geopotential with which mean sea level would coincide if the ocean were at rest. The ellipsoid is an approximation because the geoid is an irregular shape. A number of reference ellipsoids are defined for use in the field of geodesy. To specify which reference ellipsoid is being used, a grid_mapping variable should be attached to the data variable as described in Chapter 5.6 of the CF Convention.

zg_day-ap-tav-l-hxy.comment: Geopotential is the sum of the specific gravitational potential energy relative to the geoid and the specific centripetal potential energy. Geopotential height is the geopotential divided by the standard acceleration due to gravity. It is numerically similar to the altitude (or geometric height) and not to the quantity with standard name height, which is relative to the surface.

zmicroos_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.comment: carbon  concentration from the microzooplankton (<20 um) component alone
zmicroos_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Surface Mole Concentration of Microzooplankton Expressed as Carbon in Sea Water

zmisc_mon-oc-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zmisc_mon-oc-tav-l-hxy.comment: carbon from additional zooplankton component concentrations alone (e.g. Micro, meso).  Since the models all have different numbers of components, this variable has been included to provide a check for intercomparison between models since some phytoplankton groups are supersets.
zmisc_mon-oc-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Mole Concentration of Other Zooplankton Expressed as Carbon in Sea Water

zmisc_yr-oc-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean

Since the models all have different numbers of components, this variable has been included to provide a check for intercomparison between models since some phytoplankton groups are supersets.
zmisc_yr-oc-tav-l-hxy.long_name: Mole Concentration of Other Zooplankton Expressed as Carbon in Sea Water

zmiscos_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zmiscos_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.comment: carbon from additional zooplankton component concentrations alone (e.g. Micro, meso).  Since the models all have different numbers of components, this variable has been included to provide a check for intercomparison between models since some phytoplankton groups are supersets.

zmla_day-ap-tav-z0-hxy.comment: The atmosphere boundary layer thickness is the 'depth' or 'height' of the (atmosphere) planetary boundary layer.

zmlwaero_6hr-ap-tpt-l-hy.comment: longwave heating rate due to volcanic aerosols to be diagnosed through double radiation call, zonal average values required
zmlwaero_6hr-ap-tpt-l-hy.long_name: Zonal Mean Longwave Heating Rate Due to Volcanic Aerosols

zmswaero_6hr-ap-tpt-l-hy.comment: shortwave heating rate due to volcanic aerosols to be diagnosed through double radiation call, zonal average values required
zmswaero_6hr-ap-tpt-l-hy.long_name: Zonal Mean Shortwave Heating Rate Due to Volcanic Aerosols

zmtnt_mon-ap-tav-p39-hy.comment: The diabatic heating rates due to all the processes that may change potential temperature

zo2min_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zo2min_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Depth of vertical minimum concentration of dissolved oxygen gas (if two, then the shallower)

zooc_mon-oc-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zooc_mon-oc-tav-l-hxy.comment: sum of zooplankton carbon component concentrations

zooc_yr-oc-tav-l-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zooc_yr-oc-tav-l-hxy.comment: sum of zooplankton carbon component concentrations

zoocos_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zoocos_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.comment: sum of zooplankton carbon component concentrations

zos_mon-op-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zos_mon-op-tav-z0-hxy.comment: This is the dynamic sea level, so should have zero global area mean. It should not include inverse barometer depressions from sea ice.

zossq_mon-op-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zossq_mon-op-tav-z0-hxy.long_name: Square of Sea Surface Height Above Geoid

zostoga_mon-op-tav-z0-hm.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zostoga_mon-op-tav-z0-hm.comment: There is no CMIP6 request for zosga nor zossga.
zostoga_mon-op-tav-z0-hm.long_name: Global Average Thermosteric Sea Level Change

zsatarag_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zsatarag_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Depth of aragonite saturation horizon (0 if undersaturated at all depths, 'missing' if supersaturated at all depths; if multiple horizons exist, the shallowest should be taken).

zsatcalc_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.cell_methods: area: mean where sea time: mean
zsatcalc_mon-oc-tav-z0-hxy.comment: Depth of calcite saturation horizon (0 if undersaturated at all depths, and missing saturated through whole depth; if two or more horizons exist, then the shallowest is reported)

ztp_mon-ae-tav-z0-hxy.comment: 2D monthly mean thermal tropopause calculated using WMO tropopause definition on 3d temperature

zvelbase_yr-li-tav-z0-hxyA.comment: A velocity is a vector quantity. 'Upward' indicates a vector component which is positive when directed upward (negative downward). 'basal' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere
zvelbase_yr-li-tav-z0-hxyA.long_name: Upward Component of Land-Ice Basal Velocity

zvelbase_yr-li-tav-z0-hxyG.comment: A velocity is a vector quantity. 'Upward' indicates a vector component which is positive when directed upward (negative downward). 'basal' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere
zvelbase_yr-li-tav-z0-hxyG.long_name: Upward Component of Land-Ice Basal Velocity

zvelsurf_yr-li-tav-z0-hxyA.comment: A velocity is a vector quantity. 'Upward' indicates a vector component which is positive when directed upward (negative downward). The surface called 'surface' means the lower boundary of the atmosphere
zvelsurf_yr-li-tav-z0-hxyA.long_name: Upward Component of Land-Ice Surface Velocity
